    ('Markus Zusak', 'Markus Zusak is an Australian author known for his bestselling novel The Book Thief, which explores the power of words and storytelling in the midst of World War II.' ,'noPicture.png'),
    ('J.D. Salinger', 'J.D. Salinger was an American writer best known for his novel The Catcher in the Rye, a classic coming-of-age story that has had a significant impact on literature and popular culture.' ,'noPicture.png'),
    ('Paula Hawkins', 'Paula Hawkins is a British author known for her psychological thriller novel The Girl on the Train, which became a global sensation and was adapted into a successful film.' ,'noPicture.png'),
    ('Dante Alighieri', 'Dante Alighieri was an Italian poet known for his epic masterpiece The Divine Comedy, a seminal work of medieval literature that explores the journey of the soul through Hell, Purgatory, and Paradise.' ,'noPicture.png'),
    ('George R.R. Martin', 'George R.R. Martin is an American author famous for his epic fantasy series A Song of Ice and Fire, which has been adapted into the acclaimed TV series Game of Thrones.' ,'noPicture.png'),
    ('Oscar Wilde', 'Oscar Wilde was an Irish poet, playwright, and novelist known for his wit, aestheticism, and sharp social commentary, with works such as The Picture of Dorian Gray and The Importance of Being Earnest.' ,'noPicture.png'),
    ('John Steinbeck', 'John Steinbeck was an American writer and Nobel laureate, known for his realistic and social novels such as The Grapes of Wrath and Of Mice and Men.' ,'noPicture.png'),
    ('Douglas Adams', 'Douglas Adams was an English author and humorist, best known for his science fiction series The Hitchhiker''s Guide to the Galaxy, which has gained a cult following.' ,'noPicture.png'),
    ('Arthur Conan Doyle', 'Arthur Conan Doyle was a British writer and physician, best known for his detective fiction featuring the character Sherlock Holmes.' ,'noPicture.png'),
    ('Ernest Hemingway', 'Ernest Hemingway was an American novelist and short story writer, known for his concise and impactful writing style and his exploration of themes such as war, love, and masculinity.' ,'noPicture.png'),
    ('Alice Walker', 'Alice Walker is an American author and activist, known for her novel The Color Purple, which won the Pulitzer Prize for Fiction and explores issues of race, gender, and identity.' ,'noPicture.png'),
    ('Gabriel García Márquez', 'Gabriel García Márquez was a Colombian author and Nobel laureate, known for his magical realism style of writing, showcased in his masterpiece One Hundred Years of Solitude.' ,'noPicture.png'),
    ('Emily Brontë', 'Emily Brontë was an English novelist and poet, best known for her only novel Wuthering Heights, a timeless tale of love, passion, and revenge set in the moorlands of Yorkshire.' ,'noPicture.png'),
    ('Alexandre Dumas', 'Alexandre Dumas was a French writer, best known for his historical novels including The Three Musketeers and The Count of Monte Cristo, which have become classics of adventure literature.' ,'noPicture.png'),
    ('Sue Monk Kidd', 'Sue Monk Kidd is an American author known for her novels The Secret Life of Bees and The Invention of Wings, which explore themes of female empowerment, race, and social justice.' ,'noPicture.png'),
    ('Kurt Vonnegut', 'Kurt Vonnegut was an American writer known for his satirical novels such as Slaughterhouse-Five, which blend dark humor with social commentary and anti-war themes.' ,'noPicture.png'),
    ('Louisa May Alcott', 'Louisa May Alcott was an American author known for her novel Little Women, a beloved classic that depicts the lives and struggles of four sisters during the Civil War era.' ,'noPicture.png'),
    ('Stephen Hawking', 'Stephen Hawking was a renowned British physicist and author, known for his contributions to the field of theoretical physics and his bestselling book A Brief History of Time.' ,'noPicture.png'),
    ('William Golding', 'William Golding was a British novelist and Nobel laureate, best known for his novel Lord of the Flies, which explores the dark side of human nature through the story of a group of boys stranded on an uninhabited island.' ,'noPicture.png'),
    ('Charles Dickens', 'Charles Dickens was an English writer and social critic, regarded as one of the greatest novelists of the Victorian era. His works, such as A Tale of Two Cities and Great Expectations, vividly depict the social injustices and struggles of the time.' ,'noPicture.png'),
    ('Mary Shelley', 'Mary Shelley was an English novelist and short story writer, best known for her Gothic novel Frankenstein, which explores themes of creation, ambition, and the consequences of playing God.' ,'noPicture.png'),
    ('Lois Lowry', 'Lois Lowry is an American author known for her children''s and young adult books, including The Giver, a dystopian novel that tackles themes of conformity, individuality, and the power of memory.' ,'noPicture.png'),
    ('Sylvia Plath', 'Sylvia Plath was an American poet, novelist, and short story writer, known for her confessional style and exploration of themes such as mental illness, identity, and feminism. Her novel The Bell Jar is considered a classic of American literature.' ,'noPicture.png'),
    ('Nathaniel Hawthorne', 'Nathaniel Hawthorne was an American novelist and short story writer, best known for his novel The Scarlet Letter, which delves into themes of guilt, sin, and the human condition in Puritan New England.' ,'noPicture.png'),
    ('Margaret Atwood', 'Margaret Atwood is a Canadian author known for her works of speculative fiction, including The Handmaid''s Tale, a dystopian novel that examines themes of power, oppression, and gender roles in a totalitarian society.' ,'noPicture.png'),
    ('Franz Kafka', 'Franz Kafka was a German-speaking writer of novels and short stories, known for his surreal and existential works that explore themes of alienation, bureaucracy, and the human condition. His novel The Trial is a seminal work of 20th-century literature.' ,'noPicture.png'),
    ('Mark Twain', 'Mark Twain, born Samuel Clemens, was an American writer, humorist, and lecturer, best known for his novels The Adventures of Tom Sawyer and Adventures of Huckleberry Finn, which capture the essence of American life and address social issues of the time.' ,'noPicture.png'),
    ('Cormac McCarthy', 'Cormac McCarthy is an American novelist, playwright, and screenwriter, known for his dark and uncompromising storytelling style. His novels, including Blood Meridian and The Road, delve into themes of violence, survival, and the human spirit.' ,'noPicture.png'),
    ('S.E. Hinton', 'S.E. Hinton is an American writer best known for her young adult novels, including The Outsiders, a coming-of-age story that explores themes of identity, class conflict, and the bonds of friendship.' ,'noPicture.png'),
    ('Charlotte Brontë', 'Charlotte Brontë was an English novelist and poet, one of the famed Brontë sisters. She is best known for her novel Jane Eyre, a classic of Victorian literature that delves into themes of love, independence, and social class.' ,'noPicture.png'),
    ('Frances Hodgson Burnett', 'Frances Hodgson Burnett was a British-American novelist and playwright, best known for her children''s classics such as The Secret Garden and Little Lord Fauntleroy.' ,'noPicture.png'),
    ('Patrick Rothfuss', 'Patrick Rothfuss is an American writer and college lecturer, known for his epic fantasy series The Kingkiller Chronicle, which includes The Name of the Wind and The Wise Man''s Fear.' ,'noPicture.png'),
    ('Donna Tartt', 'Donna Tartt is an American writer and author of acclaimed novels, including The Secret History and The Goldfinch, which explore themes of obsession, art, and the complexities of human relationships.' ,'noPicture.png'),
    ('Alex Michaelides', 'Alex Michaelides is a British-Cypriot author and screenwriter, known for his psychological thriller novel The Silent Patient, which became a bestseller and captivated readers with its twists and turns.' ,'noPicture.png'),
    ('Tara Westover', 'Tara Westover is an American author known for her memoir Educated, which chronicles her journey from a survivalist family in rural Idaho to earning a PhD from Cambridge University, exploring themes of education, identity, and resilience.' ,'noPicture.png'),
    ('Kristin Hannah', 'Kristin Hannah is an American author of popular fiction, particularly known for her emotionally rich and engaging novels, including The Nightingale and Firefly Lane, which delve into themes of family, love, and resilience.' ,'noPicture.png'),
    ('Andy Weir', 'Andy Weir is an American writer known for his science fiction novel The Martian, which tells the story of an astronaut stranded on Mars and his struggle for survival. Weir''s work combines scientific accuracy with gripping storytelling.' ,'noPicture.png'),
    ('Virginia Woolf', 'Virginia Woolf was a British modernist writer and one of the foremost figures of literary modernism. Her novels, including Mrs. Dalloway and To the Lighthouse, explore themes of gender, identity, and the complexities of human consciousness.' ,'noPicture.png'),
    ('Ralph Ellison', 'Ralph Ellison was an American novelist, literary critic, and scholar, best known for his novel Invisible Man, which examines themes of identity, race, and social injustice in America.' ,'noPicture.png'),
    ('Truman Capote', 'Truman Capote was an American writer and playwright, known for his works of fiction and nonfiction. His novel Breakfast at Tiffany''s and true crime book In Cold Blood are considered literary classics and showcase Capote''s distinctive writing style.' ,'noPicture.png'),
    ('Toni Morrison', 'Toni Morrison was an American novelist, essayist, editor, and professor. She is best known for her critically acclaimed novels, including Beloved, Song of Solomon, and The Bluest Eye, which explore themes of race, identity, and the African American experience.' ,'noPicture.png'),
    ('Fyodor Dostoevsky', 'Fyodor Dostoevsky was a Russian novelist, philosopher, and short-story writer. His works, such as Crime and Punishment, The Brothers Karamazov, and Notes from Underground, delve into the human psyche, morality, and existentialism.' ,'noPicture.png'),
    ('Leo Tolstoy', 'Leo Tolstoy was a Russian writer and one of the most renowned authors in world literature. His novels, including War and Peace and Anna Karenina, are epic in scope and explore themes of love, society, and the human condition.' ,'noPicture.png'),
    ('Mikhail Bulgakov', 'Mikhail Bulgakov was a Russian writer and playwright, known for his satirical and fantastical works. His novel The Master and Margarita is considered a masterpiece of 20th-century literature and combines elements of satire, fantasy, and political commentary.' ,'noPicture.png'),
    ('Boris Pasternak', 'Boris Pasternak was a Russian poet, novelist, and literary translator. He is best known for his novel Doctor Zhivago, which explores the personal and political struggles of its protagonist amidst the backdrop of the Russian Revolution and World War I.' ,'noPicture.png'),
    ('Alexander Pushkin', 'Alexander Pushkin was a Russian poet, playwright, and novelist, often considered the founder of modern Russian literature. His works, including Eugene Onegin and The Bronze Horseman, showcase his mastery of verse and storytelling.' ,'noPicture.png'),
    ('Anton Chekhov', 'Anton Chekhov was a Russian playwright and short-story writer, widely regarded as one of the greatest masters of the modern short story. His plays, such as The Cherry Orchard and Three Sisters, are celebrated for their nuanced characters and realistic portrayal of human nature.' ,'noPicture.png'),
    ('Ivan Turgenev', 'Ivan Turgenev was a Russian novelist, playwright, and short-story writer. His works, including Fathers and Sons and A Month in the Country, examine themes of love, social change, and the clash between generations in 19th-century Russia.' ,'noPicture.png'),
    ('Aleksandr Solzhenitsyn', 'Aleksandr Solzhenitsyn was a Russian novelist, historian, and Nobel Prize laureate. His works, such as One Day in the Life of Ivan Denisovich and The Gulag Archipelago, expose the harsh realities of Soviet totalitarianism and serve as powerful indictments of oppression and injustice.' ,'noPicture.png'),
    ('Nikolai Gogol', 'Nikolai Gogol was a Ukrainian-born Russian writer and playwright, considered one of the most important figures in Russian literature. His works, including Dead Souls and The Overcoat, blend humor, satire, and vivid storytelling to portray the absurdities of Russian society.' ,'noPicture.png'),
    ('Yevgeny Zamyatin', 'Yevgeny Zamyatin was a Russian author and philosopher, known for his dystopian novel We. The novel depicts a future society where individualism is suppressed, and has been influential in the genre of dystopian fiction.','noPicture.png'),
    ('Mikhail Sholokhov', 'Mikhail Sholokhov was a Russian novelist and winner of the Nobel Prize in Literature. His epic novel And Quiet Flows the Don portrays the life of Don Cossacks during the Russian Revolution and Civil War.','noPicture.png'),
    ('Ilya Ilf and Evgeny Petrov', 'Ilya Ilf and Evgeny Petrov were Soviet authors who collaborated on several satirical novels, including The Twelve Chairs and The Little Golden Calf. Their works are known for their humor and social commentary.','noPicture.png'),
    ('Andrei Platonov', 'Andrei Platonov was a Russian writer and poet, known for his experimental and often challenging works. His novel The Foundation Pit explores themes of collectivism and the individual in Soviet society.','noPicture.png'),
    ('J.M. Coetzee', 'J.M. Coetzee is a South African-born novelist, essayist, and Nobel laureate. His works, such as Waiting for the Barbarians and Disgrace, examine themes of power, morality, and postcolonialism.','noPicture.png');
INSERT INTO reviews (book_id, user_id, rating, comment, review_date)
VALUES
    (86, 7, 4.0, 'Player Piano offers a fascinating glimpse into a future dominated by machines. Vonnegut''s portrayal of a society where automation rules brings up questions about the value of human labor and creativity. The characters and their struggles are relatable, making this a thought-provoking read.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (86, 2, 3.5, 'Vonnegut''s Player Piano presents a dystopian world where technology reigns supreme. The story''s commentary on class divisions and the loss of individuality is relevant even today. The narrative kept me engaged, although some moments felt a bit slow.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (86, 5, 4.5, 'Player Piano takes us on a journey through a future society where machines control every aspect of life. The themes of inequality and the erosion of human agency are powerful. Vonnegut''s sharp wit and social commentary shine in this impactful novel.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (86, 4, 3.0, 'While Player Piano raises intriguing questions about the role of humans in a technologically advanced world, I found some parts of the story hard to follow. The characters'' emotions and motivations could have been explored more deeply.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (87, 1, 5.0, 'Mother Night is a haunting exploration of morality, identity, and the blurred lines between good and evil. The protagonist''s inner turmoil is masterfully portrayed, and the narrative structure kept me engaged from start to finish. Vonnegut''s signature wit shines throughout.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (87, 2, 4.5, 'Vonnegut''s Mother Night is a gripping tale of a man caught between conflicting allegiances. The book''s exploration of the complexity of truth and the consequences of one''s actions left a profound impact on me. The ending was both thought-provoking and bittersweet.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (87, 3, 3.5, 'Mother Night offers a unique perspective on WWII and the moral ambiguity of wartime decisions. While the concept is intriguing, I found the pacing a bit uneven at times. The character development and philosophical themes, however, make it a worthwhile read.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (87, 4, 5.0, 'Vonnegut''s Mother Night delves into the complexities of human nature and the thin line between right and wrong. The story''s blend of dark humor and deep reflection makes it a captivating read. The writing style and character depth are truly exceptional.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (85, 1, 4.0, 'Breakfast of Champions is a thought-provoking and surreal journey into the mind of an author questioning his own creation. Vonnegut''s satirical narrative style adds layers of depth to the story, making it both hilarious and profound.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (85, 5, 5.0, 'Vonnegut''s Breakfast of Champions is a literary gem that challenges conventions and breaks down the boundaries between reality and fiction. The author''s exploration of existential questions through the interactions of eccentric characters is brilliant.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (85, 3, 3.5, 'Breakfast of Champions is an avant-garde work that defies traditional storytelling. While its unconventional narrative can be disorienting, it provides a unique perspective on the author-reader relationship and the blurred lines of reality.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (85, 4, 4.5, 'Vonnegut''s Breakfast of Champions is a mind-bending exploration of creativity, authorship, and the nature of existence itself. The book''s satirical take on consumerism and media is as relevant today as it was when it was written.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (84, 1, 4.5, 'Cat''s Cradle is a brilliant and thought-provoking satire that uses humor to tackle serious themes. Vonnegut''s storytelling is both whimsical and insightful, creating a memorable reading experience.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (84, 2, 5.0, 'Vonnegut''s Cat''s Cradle is a literary masterpiece that delves into the absurdity of human behavior and the consequences of scientific discovery. The Bokononist religion adds a layer of complexity to the narrative that is both intriguing and thought-provoking.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (84, 5, 4.0, 'Cat''s Cradle is a brilliant exploration of human folly and the unintended consequences of scientific advancement. Vonnegut''s dark humor and sharp wit make this book a must-read for anyone who enjoys satirical fiction.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (84, 4, 4.5, 'Vonnegut''s Cat''s Cradle is a masterclass in blending humor with profound philosophical questions. The novel''s intricate plot and diverse characters offer a unique perspective on the complexities of modern life.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (60, 1, 4.0, 'For Whom the Bell Tolls is a powerful portrayal of the brutality and heroism of war. Hemingway''s prose captures the emotional and psychological turmoil of the characters as they navigate the complexities of conflict.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (60, 2, 4.5, 'Hemingway''s For Whom the Bell Tolls is a literary masterpiece that immerses readers in the chaos and intensity of the Spanish Civil War. The characters'' struggles and the vivid descriptions of the landscape create a gripping narrative.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (60, 3, 3.5, 'For Whom the Bell Tolls is a poignant exploration of the human cost of war. Hemingway''s prose is both raw and poetic, capturing the emotional depth of the characters and the harsh realities they face.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (60, 5, 4.0, 'Hemingway''s For Whom the Bell Tolls is a harrowing depiction of the impact of war on individuals. The novel''s vivid descriptions and powerful characters make it a memorable and thought-provoking read.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (49, 6, 5.0, 'J.R.R. Tolkien''s The Hobbit is a timeless classic that takes readers on a magical journey through Middle-earth. The adventurous tale of Bilbo Baggins and his encounters with various creatures captivates the imagination.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (49, 2, 4.5, 'The Hobbit is a delightful adventure filled with memorable characters and breathtaking landscapes. Tolkien''s world-building and storytelling skills are evident in every page, creating a rich and immersive fantasy experience.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (49, 3, 5.0, 'J.R.R. Tolkien''s The Hobbit is a masterpiece of fantasy literature. The whimsical tone, detailed descriptions, and epic quests make it a must-read for anyone seeking a captivating and enchanting story.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (49, 4, 4.0, 'The Hobbit is a charming and adventurous tale that introduces readers to the captivating world of Middle-earth. Tolkien''s imaginative storytelling and vibrant characters make this a book that continues to capture hearts.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (45, 1, 4.5, 'Ernest Hemingway''s The Old Man and the Sea is a poignant and powerful novella that delves into themes of perseverance, resilience, and the connection between man and nature. The story of Santiago and his epic battle with the marlin is both heartrending and inspiring.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (45, 2, 5.0, 'The Old Man and the Sea is a beautifully written work that captures the essence of human determination and the vastness of the sea. Hemingway''s prose is elegant and evocative, immersing the reader in Santiago''s world.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (45, 3, 4.0, 'Ernest Hemingway''s The Old Man and the Sea is a classic exploration of the human spirit and the challenges we face in our pursuit of greatness. Santiago''s journey is a metaphor for life itself, a testament to the resilience of the human soul.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (45, 4, 5.0, 'The Old Man and the Sea is a timeless masterpiece that captures the essence of struggle, hope, and triumph. Hemingway''s spare and powerful prose paints a vivid picture of Santiago''s determination and the awe-inspiring forces of nature.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (2, 1, 5.0, 'Harper Lee''s To Kill a Mockingbird is a literary masterpiece that addresses the issues of racism, prejudice, and social injustice in the American South. Through the eyes of Scout Finch, the novel provides a thought-provoking perspective on the complexities of human nature and morality.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (2, 2, 4.5, 'To Kill a Mockingbird is a poignant and powerful novel that challenges societal norms and explores the innocence of childhood. Harper Lee''s characters, particularly Atticus Finch and Boo Radley, leave a lasting impact on readers.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (2, 3, 4.0, 'Harper Lee''s To Kill a Mockingbird is a timeless classic that examines the complexities of racial prejudice and moral growth. The character of Atticus Finch serves as a moral compass in a world filled with injustice.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (2, 4, 5.0, 'To Kill a Mockingbird is a thought-provoking novel that remains relevant in today''s world. Through the eyes of Scout, Jem, and Dill, Harper Lee exposes the deep-rooted prejudices and inequalities that persist in society.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (1, 1, 4.5, 'Pride and Prejudice by Jane Austen is a delightful classic that explores the complexities of societal expectations and the transformative power of love. The characters, particularly Elizabeth Bennet and Mr. Darcy, are beautifully developed and their interactions are a joy to read.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (1, 2, 5.0, 'Jane Austen''s Pride and Prejudice is a timeless novel that captivates readers with its wit, romance, and astute social commentary. The story of Elizabeth Bennet and her journey from prejudice to love is heartwarming and engaging.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (1, 5 , 4.0, 'Pride and Prejudice is a classic romance that remains relevant even today. Jane Austen''s depiction of the social norms and expectations of the Regency era, along with the budding romance between Elizabeth and Mr. Darcy, makes for a compelling read.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (1, 4, 4.5, 'Jane Austen''s Pride and Prejudice is a charming novel that skillfully satirizes the social norms of its time while also telling a captivating love story. The characters are memorable and the themes of love, class, and self-discovery are explored with depth and nuance.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (3, 6, 5.0, 'George Orwell''s 1984 is a thought-provoking dystopian novel that remains hauntingly relevant to the present day. The portrayal of a totalitarian regime and the suppression of individuality serves as a stark warning about the dangers of unchecked government power.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (3, 2, 4.5, '1984 is a powerful and disturbing novel that explores the consequences of a totalitarian society. Orwell''s depiction of a world where truth is manipulated and individuality is crushed is both gripping and cautionary.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (3, 7, 4.0, 'George Orwell''s 1984 is a chilling portrayal of a dystopian future where government control and surveillance run rampant. The novel''s themes of propaganda, thought control, and the loss of personal freedoms make it a must-read for anyone interested in the human struggle for autonomy.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (3, 4, 5.0, '1984 is a thought-provoking and cautionary tale that delves into the dangers of totalitarianism and the manipulation of truth. George Orwell''s depiction of a society stripped of individuality and privacy serves as a stark reminder of the importance of safeguarding freedom.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (4, 1, 5.0, 'F. Scott Fitzgerald''s The Great Gatsby is a masterpiece that captures the essence of the Roaring Twenties. The novel''s exploration of the American Dream, decadence, and the pursuit of unattainable desires is as relevant today as it was during its time.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (4, 2, 4.5, 'The Great Gatsby is a beautifully written novel that offers a glimpse into the excesses and disillusionments of the Jazz Age. Fitzgerald''s portrayal of the characters and their aspirations, especially Gatsby''s infatuation with Daisy, is both captivating and tragic.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (4, 3, 4.0, 'Fitzgerald''s The Great Gatsby is a poignant exploration of wealth, privilege, and the emptiness that can lie beneath the glamorous surface. The characters'' pursuit of the American Dream and their ultimate disillusionment make for a compelling and reflective read.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (4, 4, 5.0, 'The Great Gatsby is a classic novel that delves into the complexities of social class, love, and the illusion of the American Dream. Fitzgerald''s prose is both lyrical and introspective, creating a memorable and thought-provoking narrative.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (5, 1, 5.0, 'J.R.R. Tolkien''s The Lord of the Rings is an epic fantasy masterpiece that transports readers to a magical realm filled with rich lore, captivating characters, and a battle between good and evil. The intricate world-building and the journey of Frodo and the Fellowship make this series an enduring favorite.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (5, 2, 4.5, 'The Lord of the Rings is a literary gem that immerses readers in a world of bravery, friendship, and the battle against darkness. Tolkien''s attention to detail and the epic scope of the story make it an unforgettable reading experience.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (5, 3, 5.0, 'Tolkien''s The Lord of the Rings is a monumental achievement in fantasy literature. The intricate storytelling, the depth of the characters, and the epic quest to destroy the One Ring are elements that continue to captivate readers of all ages.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (5, 4, 4.0, 'The Lord of the Rings is a timeless tale of heroism, sacrifice, and the power of friendship. Tolkien''s masterful world-building and the rich tapestry of Middle-earth create a reading experience that transports readers to another world.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (8, 1, 5.0, 'J.K. Rowling''s Harry Potter and the Philosopher''s Stone introduces readers to the magical world of Hogwarts, where young wizards and witches embark on exciting adventures. The enchanting storyline, relatable characters, and Rowling''s imaginative writing make this book a delightful read.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (8, 2, 4.5, 'The first book in the Harry Potter series is a captivating start to a magical journey. Rowling''s ability to create a world filled with wonder, friendship, and the battle between good and evil is truly commendable.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (8, 3, 4.8, 'Harry Potter and the Philosopher''s Stone is a spellbinding tale that transports readers to a world of magic and adventure. Rowling''s storytelling prowess and her knack for creating relatable characters are evident from the very beginning of the series.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (8, 4, 5.0, 'Rowling''s debut novel, Harry Potter and the Philosopher''s Stone, is a delightful introduction to the world of wizards and witches. The enchanting plot, endearing characters, and sense of wonder make it a must-read for fantasy enthusiasts.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (17, 1, 4.0, 'Aldous Huxley''s Brave New World is a thought-provoking dystopian novel that explores the consequences of a highly controlled and engineered society. The book raises important questions about individuality, freedom, and the cost of pursuing a utopian ideal.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (17, 2, 4.2, 'Brave New World presents a chilling vision of a future society where pleasure and stability are paramount, but at the expense of authentic human experiences. Huxley''s commentary on technology, conformity, and the nature of happiness remains relevant to this day.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (17, 3, 4.5, 'Huxley''s Brave New World paints a vivid picture of a world driven by consumerism, instant gratification, and social conditioning. The story serves as a cautionary tale about the potential dangers of sacrificing individuality and critical thinking for the sake of societal harmony.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (17, 4, 3.8, 'Brave New World offers readers a glimpse into a future where technological advancement and hedonism lead to a loss of genuine human connections. The novel''s exploration of the trade-offs between happiness and authenticity is both thought-provoking and unsettling.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (19, 1, 4.5, 'The Book Thief by Markus Zusak is a deeply moving novel set during World War II, narrated by Death. The story follows Liesel Meminger, a young girl living in Nazi Germany, and her love for books and storytelling. The book explores themes of humanity, friendship, and the power of words.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (19, 2, 4.8, 'The Book Thief is a poignant and beautifully written story that captures the hardships and resilience of characters living in a war-torn world. The friendship between Liesel and Max, a Jewish fist-fighter hiding in her basement, is both heartwarming and heartbreaking.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (19, 3, 4.7, 'Markus Zusak''s The Book Thief is a masterpiece that touches the heart and soul. It skillfully portrays the small acts of kindness and beauty that can shine through even in the darkest of times. The book is a testament to the power of literature and its ability to provide solace.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (19, 4, 4.2, 'The Book Thief is a novel that captures the essence of humanity amidst the brutality of war. It beautifully portrays the strength of the human spirit and the way that words can create connections and offer solace even in the midst of suffering.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (72, 1, 4.6, 'Fyodor Dostoevsky''s "The Idiot" is a complex and thought-provoking novel that delves into the intricacies of human nature and morality. Prince Myshkin, the titular "idiot," is a character whose innocence and purity clash with the complexities of society. The novel explores themes of love, mental illness, and societal norms.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (72, 2, 4.3, 'Reading "The Idiot" is like diving into the depths of the human psyche. Dostoevsky''s exploration of the tension between inner morality and external societal norms is truly captivating. The characters are deeply flawed yet fascinating, and the novel''s exploration of human connection is profound.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (72, 3, 4.7, 'Dostoevsky''s "The Idiot" is a novel that delves into the complexities of the human soul. Prince Myshkin is a unique protagonist whose innocence and goodness stand out against a backdrop of deceit and corruption. The novel''s exploration of human relationships and the search for meaning is both poignant and thought-provoking.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (72, 4, 4.5, 'Fyodor Dostoevsky''s "The Idiot" is a masterpiece that delves into the moral and ethical dilemmas faced by its characters. Prince Myshkin is a character who challenges societal conventions and norms, leading to a deep exploration of human nature and the complexities of social interactions.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (75, 1, 4.2, '"Dead Souls" by Nikolai Gogol is a satirical masterpiece that offers a unique glimpse into 19th-century Russian society. The novel follows the enigmatic Chichikov as he traverses the Russian countryside, acquiring "dead souls" in a scheme that reflects the absurdities of the era. Gogol''s wit and social commentary make this a timeless work of literature.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (75, 2, 4.5, 'Nikolai Gogol''s "Dead Souls" is a brilliant satire that highlights the flaws and idiosyncrasies of Russian society. Chichikov''s absurd plan to buy and sell "dead souls" is a metaphor for the moral decay and hypocrisy of the time. Gogol''s vivid characters and sharp wit make this novel a must-read.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (75, 3, 4.0, '"Dead Souls" is a darkly humorous and insightful commentary on human greed and the societal structures of 19th-century Russia. Gogol''s characters, especially the enigmatic Chichikov, embody the complexity and contradictions of the era. This novel remains relevant for its astute observations on human nature.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (75, 4, 4.3, 'Nikolai Gogol''s "Dead Souls" is a brilliant work that blends satire, social critique, and humor. Chichikov''s quest to acquire "dead souls" is a mirror reflecting the vices and absurdities of the time. Gogol''s writing style and keen observations make this novel a thought-provoking and engaging read.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (75, 1, 4.2, '"Dead Souls" by Nikolai Gogol is a satirical masterpiece that offers a unique glimpse into 19th-century Russian society. The novel follows the enigmatic Chichikov as he traverses the Russian countryside, acquiring "dead souls" in a scheme that reflects the absurdities of the era. Gogol''s wit and social commentary make this a timeless work of literature.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (75, 2, 4.5, 'Nikolai Gogol''s "Dead Souls" is a brilliant satire that highlights the flaws and idiosyncrasies of Russian society. Chichikov''s absurd plan to buy and sell "dead souls" is a metaphor for the moral decay and hypocrisy of the time. Gogol''s vivid characters and sharp wit make this novel a must-read.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (75, 3, 4.0, '"Dead Souls" is a darkly humorous and insightful commentary on human greed and the societal structures of 19th-century Russia. Gogol''s characters, especially the enigmatic Chichikov, embody the complexity and contradictions of the era. This novel remains relevant for its astute observations on human nature.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (75, 4, 4.3, 'Nikolai Gogol''s "Dead Souls" is a brilliant work that blends satire, social critique, and humor. Chichikov''s quest to acquire "dead souls" is a mirror reflecting the vices and absurdities of the time. Gogol''s writing style and keen observations make this novel a thought-provoking and engaging read.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (23, 1, 4.7, '"A Game of Thrones" by George R.R. Martin is a masterfully crafted epic fantasy that weaves together intricate political intrigue, rich character development, and unexpected plot twists. The intricate web of alliances and power struggles in the Seven Kingdoms is riveting, and Martin''s realistic characters make the story truly captivating.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (23, 2, 4.5, 'George R.R. Martin''s "A Game of Thrones" introduces readers to a complex and sprawling fantasy world that is as unpredictable as it is immersive. The struggle for power and the constant shifting of allegiances keep readers engaged, while the well-defined characters and their growth add depth to the narrative.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (23, 3, 4.8, 'In "A Game of Thrones," George R.R. Martin transports readers to a meticulously crafted world filled with political scheming, complex characters, and breathtaking fantasy elements. The intricate plotlines and morally ambiguous characters make this epic tale a must-read for fans of the genre.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (23, 4, 4.6, '"A Game of Thrones" by George R.R. Martin is a mesmerizing introduction to the "A Song of Ice and Fire" series. The intertwining stories of noble families, alongside dragons and direwolves, create an irresistible narrative. Martin''s ability to surprise readers and subvert fantasy tropes is a testament to his storytelling prowess.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (35, 1, 4.5, '"Slaughterhouse-Five" by Kurt Vonnegut is a poignant and unconventional anti-war novel that defies traditional narrative structures. Vonnegut''s blend of science fiction, dark humor, and insightful commentary on the horrors of war make this a thought-provoking read. The book''s nonlinear structure adds to its impact and leaves a lasting impression.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (35, 2, 4.8, 'Kurt Vonnegut''s "Slaughterhouse-Five" is a powerful anti-war novel that challenges the notion of linear time and explores the trauma of war through a unique narrative lens. The protagonist''s journey through time, along with Vonnegut''s signature wit, creates a gripping and introspective reading experience.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (35, 3, 4.7, 'Vonnegut''s "Slaughterhouse-Five" is a tour de force that combines satirical humor, sci-fi elements, and deep philosophical questions about the human condition. The story of Billy Pilgrim''s experiences during World War II and his time-traveling adventures creates a profound exploration of the senselessness of war and the complexities of existence.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (35, 4, 4.6, 'In "Slaughterhouse-Five," Kurt Vonnegut presents a masterclass in blending absurdity with tragedy. The novel''s nonlinear structure mirrors the disjointed memories of its protagonist, capturing the chaotic essence of war. Vonnegut''s sharp social commentary and unique narrative style make this a timeless and thought-provoking work.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (64, 1, 4.5, '"Crime and Punishment" by Fyodor Dostoevsky is a psychological masterpiece that delves into the depths of human nature and morality. The complex character of Raskolnikov and his inner turmoil make for a gripping exploration of guilt, redemption, and the consequences of one''s actions.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (64, 2, 4.8, 'Dostoevsky''s "Crime and Punishment" is a profound examination of the human psyche, morality, and the blurred line between right and wrong. The novel''s vivid characters and intricate plot keep readers engaged while prompting reflection on the ethical dilemmas faced by its protagonist.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (64, 3, 4.7, '"Crime and Punishment" is a compelling work that immerses readers in the moral quandaries faced by its characters. Dostoevsky''s exploration of guilt and redemption, set against the backdrop of 19th-century Russia, offers a timeless and thought-provoking reading experience.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (64, 4, 4.6, 'In "Crime and Punishment," Dostoevsky weaves a gripping narrative that delves into the psychological complexities of its characters. Raskolnikov''s internal struggle and the ethical dilemmas he faces are as relevant today as they were in the 19th century, making this a must-read for anyone interested in deep philosophical themes.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (61, 1, 4.2, '"Invisible Man" by Ralph Ellison is a thought-provoking exploration of identity, race, and social injustice. The protagonist''s journey from invisibility to self-discovery is a powerful metaphor for the struggles faced by marginalized individuals in a discriminatory society.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (61, 2, 4.5, 'Ellison''s "Invisible Man" is a groundbreaking novel that tackles issues of racism and identity in a deeply impactful way. The protagonist''s journey to find his place in a racially divided society resonates with readers of all backgrounds and continues to be relevant in today''s world.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (61, 3, 4.3, 'With "Invisible Man," Ralph Ellison provides a searing portrayal of the African American experience in a racially charged America. The book''s exploration of invisibility as both a physical and metaphorical concept offers profound insights into the challenges faced by marginalized communities.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (61, 4, 4.4, 'Ralph Ellison''s "Invisible Man" is a timeless and impactful novel that tackles issues of identity, racism, and societal expectations. Through the protagonist''s struggle to find his voice, the novel sheds light on the complex and often hidden layers of discrimination in American society.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (46, 1, 3.8, '"The Metamorphosis" by Franz Kafka is a surreal and thought-provoking novella that delves into themes of isolation and alienation. The protagonist''s transformation into a giant insect serves as a metaphor for the disconnect between an individual and society.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (46, 2, 4.0, 'Kafka''s "The Metamorphosis" is a haunting exploration of existential crisis and the absurdity of human existence. The novel raises questions about identity, purpose, and the search for meaning in a world that often feels nonsensical.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (46, 3, 3.5, 'In "The Metamorphosis," Kafka presents a bleak and unsettling portrayal of the individual''s struggle to find his place in a world that rejects him. The novella invites readers to contemplate themes of self-worth, family dynamics, and the human condition.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (46, 4, 3.7, 'Franz Kafka''s "The Metamorphosis" is a masterpiece of existential literature that challenges conventional notions of reality and identity. Through the protagonist''s transformation, the novella explores the fragility of human relationships and the isolation of the individual.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (41, 1, 4.2, '"Frankenstein" by Mary Shelley is a timeless classic that explores the ethical and moral implications of scientific discovery. The novel raises questions about the boundaries of knowledge and the responsibilities of creators towards their creations.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (41, 2, 4.5, 'Mary Shelley''s "Frankenstein" is a thought-provoking narrative that delves into themes of ambition, hubris, and the consequences of unchecked scientific experimentation. The book''s portrayal of the relationship between Victor Frankenstein and his creature remains compelling and relevant today.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (41, 3, 3.8, '"Frankenstein" is a cautionary tale that reflects on the dangers of playing god and meddling with the natural order. Mary Shelley''s narrative explores themes of isolation, the pursuit of knowledge, and the complex interplay between creator and creation.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (41, 4, 4.1, 'In "Frankenstein," Mary Shelley presents a gripping tale of science and hubris, exploring themes of identity and societal rejection. The novel serves as a reminder of the consequences that arise from the unchecked pursuit of knowledge and the manipulation of life.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (51, 1, 4.7, '"Jane Eyre" by Charlotte Brontë is a beautifully written novel that captures the struggles and triumphs of its titular character. The story is a poignant exploration of love, social class, and personal growth, and it continues to resonate with readers of all ages.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (51, 2, 4.6, 'Charlotte Brontë''s "Jane Eyre" is a timeless classic that showcases the strength and resilience of its protagonist. The novel''s themes of love, identity, and morality are as relevant today as they were when the book was first published.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (51, 3, 4.8, '"Jane Eyre" is a masterfully crafted novel that explores the complexities of human relationships and societal norms. Charlotte Brontë''s vivid characters and evocative prose make this a must-read for anyone seeking a compelling story filled with emotional depth.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (51, 4, 4.5, 'In "Jane Eyre," Charlotte Brontë weaves a tale of a young woman''s journey to self-discovery and independence. The novel''s exploration of gender roles, morality, and the pursuit of happiness remains as relevant today as it was during the Victorian era.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 30) DAY)),
    (29, 1, 4.20, 'A compelling story that captures the essence of the Lost Generation. The characters'' struggles and emotions are portrayed with depth.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 365) DAY)),
    (29, 2, 3.80, 'Hemingway''s writing style is unique and impactful. The novel delves into themes of love, disillusionment, and the search for meaning.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 365) DAY)),
    (29, 3, 2.50, 'I found the characters'' actions and decisions frustrating at times. The lack of clear resolutions left me wanting more.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 365) DAY)),
    (29, 4, 4.00, 'A vivid portrayal of the expatriate life in 1920s Paris and Spain. The novel captures the complexities of relationships and the challenges of the era.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 365) DAY)),
    (29, 5, 3.20, 'While the prose is evocative, the lack of a clear plot direction made the story feel disjointed. The characters'' struggles were intriguing.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 365) DAY)),
    (29, 6, 4.50, 'A masterful exploration of post-war disillusionment and the search for identity. Hemingway''s sparse prose creates a haunting atmosphere.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 365) DAY)),
    (29, 7, 3.60, 'The novel''s depiction of the ''lost'' generation is impactful. However, the detached narrative style made it challenging to connect with the characters.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 365) DAY)),
    (29, 8, 2.80, 'I struggled to fully engage with the characters and their experiences. The setting and historical context were intriguing, but the pacing felt slow.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 365) DAY)),
    (31, 1, 4.80, 'An enchanting and surreal tale that weaves together generations of the Buendía family. García Márquez''s magical realism is captivating.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 365) DAY)),
    (31, 2, 3.50, 'While the writing is beautiful, the nonlinear narrative made the story confusing at times. The symbolism and themes are thought-provoking.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 365) DAY)),
    (31, 3, 5.00, 'A literary masterpiece that immerses readers in a richly imaginative world. The characters'' journeys are both poignant and unforgettable.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 365) DAY)),
    (31, 4, 4.20, 'García Márquez''s storytelling is unparalleled. The blending of magical elements with historical events creates a unique and captivating narrative.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 365) DAY)),
    (31, 5, 3.80, 'The complexity of the Buendía family''s story can be overwhelming at times. The novel raises thought-provoking questions about time and memory.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 365) DAY)),
    (31, 6, 4.50, 'The novel''s exploration of solitude, love, and human nature is both profound and mesmerizing. García Márquez''s prose is a delight to read.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 365) DAY)),
    (31, 7, 2.60, 'The book''s dreamlike narrative style created a disconnect for me. While the prose is beautiful, the story''s meandering plot left me wanting more.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 365) DAY)),
    (31, 8, 4.10, 'A true literary masterpiece that challenges traditional storytelling conventions. The novel''s themes of solitude and destiny resonate deeply.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 365) DAY)),
    (32, 1, 4.50, 'A dark and passionate tale of love and revenge. The moody atmosphere and complex characters make for a compelling read.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 365) DAY)),
    (32, 2, 3.20, 'While the novel''s gothic elements are captivating, the tumultuous relationships and tragic events left me emotionally drained.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 365) DAY)),
    (32, 3, 4.80, 'Emily Brontë''s exploration of human emotions and the haunting setting of the moors create an unforgettable reading experience.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 365) DAY)),
    (32, 4, 2.60, 'The relentless nature of the characters'' obsession with each other became tiresome. The novel''s darkness and intensity may not be for everyone.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 365) DAY)),
    (32, 5, 4.00, 'A classic love story that delves into the depths of passion and despair. The vivid descriptions of the moors add to the novel''s atmosphere.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 365) DAY)),
    (32, 6, 3.70, 'The novel''s complex narrative structure and unlikable characters made it a challenging read. However, the themes of love and vengeance are timeless.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 365) DAY)),
    (32, 7, 4.20, 'A powerful and evocative portrayal of love and its destructive consequences. Brontë''s writing captures the raw emotions of the characters.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 365) DAY)),
    (32, 8, 3.90, 'Wuthering Heights is a dark and haunting tale that explores the darker aspects of human nature and the complexity of human relationships.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 365) DAY)),
    (27, 1, 4.50, 'A hilarious and mind-bending journey through space and time. Adams'' wit and creativity shine in this science fiction classic.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 365) DAY)),
    (27, 2, 3.80, 'While the humor is a highlight, the story felt disjointed at times. Still, the quirky characters and unique plot make it a fun read.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 365) DAY)),
    (27, 3, 4.20, 'Douglas Adams'' wit and satire make for an entertaining read, but the novel''s randomness may not be to everyone''s taste.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 365) DAY)),
    (27, 4, 3.00, 'The absurdity of the plot and characters can be amusing, but the lack of a cohesive narrative left me feeling unsatisfied.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 365) DAY)),
    (28, 1, 4.80, 'Sherlock Holmes'' deductive reasoning and Watson''s narration create a dynamic duo. Doyle''s mysteries are timeless and engaging.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 365) DAY)),
    (28, 2, 4.50, 'Classic mysteries that keep you guessing until the end. The intricate plots and Sherlock''s genius make for an immersive experience.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 365) DAY)),
    (28, 3, 3.60, 'While the mysteries are intriguing, the writing style is a bit formal and dated. Sherlock Holmes remains a brilliant character nonetheless.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 365) DAY)),
    (28, 4, 4.20, 'Holmes'' logical deductions and the Victorian setting add charm to the stories. Each case is a puzzle that keeps the reader engaged.', DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL FLOOR(RAND() * 365) DAY));
